PN,44702
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F447A1779822664
OL,3,CDonaldson set for court appearance for
OL,4,Copening of sex offences trial
OL,6,FThe former MP's wife Lady Eleanor
OL,7,FDonaldson denies charges of aiding and
OL,8,Fabetting in her husband's alleged
OL,9,Foffences.
OL,11,FSince the couple were charged most of
OL,12,Fthe hearings have been centred on her
OL,13,Fill health.
OL,15,FLast week, after weighing up all the
OL,16,Fevidence, which included medical
OL,17,Freports submitted by the defence and
OL,18,Fprosecution, Judge Paul Ramsey ruled
OL,19,Fthe 60-year-old was unfit to stand
OL,20,Ftrial.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G2/7
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,448,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44703
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F447A1779822664
OL,3,CDonaldson set for court appearance for
OL,4,Copening of sex offences trial
OL,6,FHe opted, under the 1986 Mental Health
OL,7,FOrder, to hold a trial of the facts -
OL,8,Fwhich will run at the same as her
OL,9,Fhusband's.
OL,11,F"The interests of justice require that
OL,12,Fthis case be progressed in a manner
OL,13,Fthat is fair to all parties, but also
OL,14,Fas expeditiously as such fairness
OL,15,Fpermits,'' the judge said last week.
OL,17,F"Accordingly I rule that the trial of
OL,18,FJeffrey Donaldson and the trial of the
OL,19,Ffacts of Eleanor Donaldson be held
OL,20,Fsimultaneously....''
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G3/7
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,448,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44704
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F447A1779822664
OL,3,CDonaldson set for court appearance for
OL,4,Copening of sex offences trial
OL,6,FA trial of the facts - unlike a normal
OL,7,Ftrial - happens when someone has been
OL,8,Fdeclared unfit on mental health
OL,9,Fgrounds. A jury cannot find the person
OL,10,Fguilty, instead they must determine if
OL,11,Fthey committed the alleged act. They
OL,12,Fcan also be acquitted.
OL,14,FSentencing is also different - no
OL,15,Fprison - it is either a number of
OL,16,Ftreatment orders or absolute discharge.
OL,18,FLike a normal trial, the accused will
OL,19,Fbe represented by lawyers, but will
OL,20,Fnot play any part in proceedings.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G4/7
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
